President Barack Obama has announced his intent to appoint Sondra Myers and Jackie Norris to key administration posts. Sondra Myers is currently the Senior Fellow for International, Civic and Cultural Projects at the University of Scranton and the Director of its Schemel Forum. She has previously held positions at the University of Maryland and Rutgers University, as well as serving as Special Assistant to the Chairman for Partnerships at the National Endowment for the Humanities and Cultural Advisor to Pennsylvania Governor Robert P. Casey. Jackie Norris is currently the Executive Director of the Points of Light Corporate Institute and an Adjunct Professor at American University's School of Public Affairs. She has previously served as Senior Advisor to the CEO of the Corporation for National and Community Service and Assistant to the President and Chief of Staff to the First Lady. Norris also worked as the Iowa State Director during the 2008 Presidential Campaign and as a high school government teacher in Iowa. Both Myers and Norris bring a wealth of experience and expertise to their respective positions.